#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring email for a realm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"{project_name} sends emails to users to verify their email addresses, when "
"they forget their passwords, or when an administrator needs to receive "
"notifications about a server event. To enable {project_name} to send emails, "
"you provide {project_name} with your SMTP server settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Click the *Email* tab."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#, no-wrap
msgid "Email tab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "image:{project_images}/email-tab.png[Email Tab]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Fill in the fields and toggle the switches as needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Host"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Host* denotes the SMTP server hostname used for sending emails.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Port"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Port* denotes the SMTP server port.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "From"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*From* denotes the address used for the *From* SMTP-Header for the emails sent.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "From Display Name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*From Display Name* allows to configure a user friendly email address aliases (optional). If not set the plain *From* email address will be displayed in email clients.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reply To"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Reply To* denotes the address used for the *Reply-To* SMTP-Header for the mails sent (optional). If not set the plain *From* email address will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reply To Display Name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Reply To Display Name* allows to configure a user friendly email address aliases (optional). If not set the plain *Reply To* email address will be displayed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Envelope From"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Envelope From* denotes the https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bounce_address[Bounce Address] used for the *Return-Path* SMTP-Header for the mails sent (optional).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable SSL and Enable StartTSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Toggle one of these switches to *ON* to support sending emails for "
"recovering usernames and passwords, especially if the SMTP server is on an "
"external network. You will most likely need to change the *Port* to 465, the "
"default port for SSL/TLS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Set this switch to *ON* if your SMTP server requires authentication. When "
"prompted, supply the *Username* and *Password*. The value of the *Password* "
"field can refer a value from an external <<_vault-administration,vault>>."
msgstr ""
